@jreback The default approach is a `goal_time` of `2s`, which I've reduced to `0.2s` here. There is an option to explicitly set the number of iterations, but that's not (currently) settable from the command line (nor is `goal_time`).

I probably won't be able to get to a comparison analysis until this weekend, at best.

@jorisvandenbossche Ah, awesome - I had not tried windows. `asv` also supports Python 3, but the translated `vbench` suite (unsurprisingly) looks like it'll need some work to get that running.
